###How to fix the App Dependencies issue of minimist:1.2.5 of pkg:npm/minimist@1.2.5 in nginx web server and which owasp top 10 web 2021 category this issue belong to ?
To fix the App Dependencies issue of **minimist:1.2.5 of pkg:npm/minimist@1.2.5** in nginx web server, you can try the following:

* Update the version of minimist to a newer version. The latest version of minimist is 1.2.6.
* Lock the version of minimist in your package.json file. This will prevent the version of minimist from being updated automatically.
* Use a different package manager that does not install dependencies automatically. For example, you could use yarn or pnpm.

This issue belongs to the **A3:Injection** category of the OWASP Top 10 web vulnerabilities. This category is concerned with vulnerabilities that allow attackers to inject malicious code into a web application.

Here are some additional steps you can take to mitigate this issue:

* Use a content security policy (CSP) to restrict the types of scripts that can be loaded by your web application.
* Use a web application firewall (WAF) to filter out malicious traffic.
* Keep your web application software up to date.

It is also important to note that the App Dependencies issue is not specific to nginx web servers. It can affect any web server that uses the minimist package.
